Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a #pot{} of @salted water{} for the rigatoni.

Halve and peel the @onion{1}. Cut each half into three wedges and separate the layers.

Trim the @carrot{1} and halve lengthways. Chop widthways into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Quarter the @mushrooms{150%g}. Halve any larger quarters.

Spread the veg on a lined #baking tray{}. Toss together with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Roast until tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

When the water is boiling, add the @dried rigatoni{180%g} and bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pot, off the heat.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to prevent sticking.

== Pomodoro Sauce ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @chives{5%g} (use scissors if you prefer).

Place a #pan{} over medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Fry the garlic and @tomato paste{1%tin} until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Next add the @passata{1%pack}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet}, @Worcester sauce{1%sachet}, @water{150%ml} and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (double both for 4p).

Simmer the sauce until thickened slightly, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}.

== To Serve ==

Add the roasted veg and pasta to the sauce.

Cook, stirring, until coated and warmed through, ~{1%minute}.

Divide the pasta between plates.

Garnish with a sprinkling of @grated cheese{50%g} and chives.